12/12/2022, 09:06 - Duncan: Joe the Snake slithered up to the Wordle board,
His beady eyes fixed on the jumbled letters hoard.
He'd heard that Wordle was the game to beat,
And Joe was determined to cheat and cheat.

He whispered words to his friends in the grass,
But they quickly scattered, too afraid to last.
Joe thought he had the game all sewn up,
But he hadn't reckoned on the Wordle judge's sharp eyes and pluck.

The judge was handsome and wise as an owl,
And he spotted Joe's cheating in a single scowl.
He called out Joe and asked him to explain,
But Joe just coiled and hissed in vain.

The judge declared Joe the loser fair and square,
And Joe slithered off in shame and despair.
He'd thought he was sly, but he was just a snake,
And at Wordle, he was nothing but fake.

04/08/2023, 10:46 - Big Al Goulding: Teetering on the precipice that separates despair from greatness.

I found myself there but a few months ago. Just needed a 3 or 4 on the final day to land on the other side and push Alex off the top of the 'Wordle's Greatest' plinth.

Instead, self-doubt weighed me down like a pair of cheap Argos ankle weights and I only just managed to hang onto the other side by my fingernails, cursed to share the podium with Wotherspoon for all time.

Until now.

Will you leap across to eternal glory? Or will the imp of uncertainty grab at your Next chinos as you push off - just a little tug - and you fall into the chasm of ignominy?

There's not a spreadsheet in the world that can tell you what to do, Dunc. 

In the words of convicted sex offender, R Kelly, just believe you can fly...

You may not know that for the past year our very own Super-Claire has been diligently completing Wordle whilst casually walking the entire UK coastal path!

This amazing journey of 5000+ miles is in support of two homelessness charities and is due to be completed _this_ Saturday. What an incredible inspiration!

Please donate if you can and share to friends, family, work and loose acquaintances to help smash the Â£25k goal - Woohoo!!!
